doc.after: Labradorite Ca Na Al Si 4O8 is a feldspar mineral of the plagioclase series Here a piece of labradorite displays a typical iridescence termed labradorescence caused by the refraction of light within the crystal Gemstone varieties of labradorite exhibit high degrees of iridescence and are called spectrolites moonstones or sunstones
